net.matuschek.http
Class DownloadRuleSet

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--net.matuschek.http.DownloadRuleSet
public class DownloadRuleSet
extends java.lang.Object

This download selector decides if a file should be downloaded based on the mime type and the size of the content (content-length header)

public void addRule(java.lang.String mimeBaseType,
                    java.lang.String mimeSubtype,
                    int minSize,
                    int maxSize,
                    boolean allow)
adds a download rule for the given mimetype/subtype
Parameters:
mimeType - basic mime type (the part before /)
mimeSubtype - mime sub type (part after /)
minSize - minimal size (in bytes)
maxSize - maximal size (in bytes)
allow - allow or deny this download ? wildchar "*" can be used as mimeType and mimeSubtype that means "all". there will be no pattern matching, that means "*" matches all types, but "t*" doesn't match all types that start with t
